27:32.700 --> 27:34.630
backstories of any fooler.

27:34.630 --> 27:35.870
Check it out.

27:37.800 --> 27:39.670
- I'm Adam Cheyer,

27:39.670 --> 27:41.300
co-creator of Siri,

27:41.300 --> 27:43.670
the voice assistant
on Apple devices.

27:43.670 --> 27:46.670
I started out with magic
at nine years old.

27:46.670 --> 27:48.270
A Rubik's Cube.

27:48.270 --> 27:50.170
For me, that was
a form of magic.

27:50.170 --> 27:53.370
And, in fact, the first piece
of software I ever wrote,

27:53.370 --> 27:56.800
was a program
to solve Rubik's Cube.

27:56.800 --> 27:59.900
Entrepreneurs and magicians
are very similar.

27:59.900 --> 28:02.770
Both have to imagine
an impossible future

28:02.770 --> 28:04.700
and the technology behind it.

28:04.700 --> 28:07.900
Many of my creations
were things that people

28:07.900 --> 28:09.430
did not believe were possible.

28:09.430 --> 28:11.800
That really shows
the relationship between

28:11.800 --> 28:14.700
technology and magic.

28:18.600 --> 28:21.870
- Please welcome
Siri-ous contender,

28:21.870 --> 28:23.930
Adam Cheyer.

28:26.770 --> 28:28.000
- Hello.

28:28.000 --> 28:32.270
I'm here today
to reveal to you my secrets.

28:32.270 --> 28:34.930
Entrepreneurs.

28:34.930 --> 28:37.630
The first thing
when you have a big idea

28:37.630 --> 28:40.370
is you need
to create a prototype

28:40.370 --> 28:44.570
that shows the world
of your future idea.

28:44.570 --> 28:46.730
I've happened
to bring with me today

28:46.730 --> 28:49.170
my first prototype of Siri.

28:49.170 --> 28:50.930
Would you like to see it?
- Yes.

28:52.270 --> 28:55.700
- I keep it in a little box.

28:57.870 --> 29:01.400
Once you have an idea
and a prototype,

29:01.400 --> 29:04.570
you need investors to fund
your id--your company.

29:04.570 --> 29:06.630
Penn and Teller,
would you join me on stage?

29:06.630 --> 29:08.970
You can be the ones
I'm trying to impress.

29:16.700 --> 29:19.670
I'm gonna mix these cards,
give them a shuffle.

29:28.570 --> 29:33.400
When I started Siri in 2007,

29:33.400 --> 29:35.170
people would say,

29:35.170 --> 29:37.670
"I have Google.
I have an iPhone.

29:37.670 --> 29:39.600
Why do I need anything else?"

29:39.600 --> 29:43.630
And I said, "Siri will be
better in three ways."

29:43.630 --> 29:46.000
First, when you put a keyword
into a search engine,

29:46.000 --> 29:47.830
it just gives you links.

29:47.830 --> 29:50.700
Siri is gonna
answer the question.

29:50.700 --> 29:55.100
Number two, I want to be able
to handle multiple tasks

29:55.100 --> 29:56.900
at the same time.

29:56.900 --> 29:59.730
And number three,
I want to be able to refine

29:59.730 --> 30:02.470
my questions conversationally.
"How about Tuesday?

30:02.470 --> 30:04.030
What about the next day?"

30:04.030 --> 30:05.930
Would you help me, Teller,

30:05.930 --> 30:08.300
and just choose any card
from the shuffled deck?

30:08.300 --> 30:11.030
Just--but don't look at it,
just pull it out of the deck.

30:12.700 --> 30:17.100
Okay and let's choose a card
for Penn as well.

30:21.400 --> 30:24.030
Let me show you how
this is going to work.

30:24.030 --> 30:27.900
On the back of every card,
I have a little button.

30:27.900 --> 30:30.200
What you do is you press it.

30:30.200 --> 30:31.430
Doo, doo.

30:31.430 --> 30:33.530
No, I was just kidding.

30:33.530 --> 30:36.530
We didn't actually implement
speech recognition

30:36.530 --> 30:38.800
in our first prototype of Siri.

30:38.800 --> 30:41.100
It turns out some people
don't actually like

30:41.100 --> 30:43.530
to talk to phones.

30:43.530 --> 30:46.330
But no matter.

30:46.330 --> 30:49.370
No worries, you can actually
type your questions.

30:49.370 --> 30:52.630
So Teller,
you chose a card at random.

30:52.630 --> 30:56.430
