33:14.700 --> 33:17.730
Siri says, clubs.

33:17.730 --> 33:22.430
And every card in the deck
has exactly one match.

33:22.430 --> 33:26.230
And if you chose
the black seven of clubs,

33:26.230 --> 33:29.330
the match would be the--
the other black seven.

33:29.330 --> 33:31.870
The black seven of spades.

33:36.930 --> 33:39.200
And that means
the card that you chose

33:39.200 --> 33:41.170
would be the black...

33:44.270 --> 33:45.830
Thank you very much.
- Thank you so much, man.

33:45.830 --> 33:47.730
Thank you.
- Thank you.

33:47.730 --> 33:50.730
- Adam Cheyer.

33:54.700 --> 33:57.030
Hi.
Nice to meet you.

33:57.030 --> 33:59.330
You could stay in bed
for the rest of your life

33:59.330 --> 34:02.200
and do nothing else
and still be very impressive.

34:02.200 --> 34:04.430
- Yeah,
I aspire to be a magician

34:04.430 --> 34:05.830
like all the others
on this stage.

34:05.830 --> 34:07.570
- That's amazing.

34:07.570 --> 34:10.230
Um, I have so many questions
about Siri.

34:10.230 --> 34:12.170
Like, sometimes
you can get Siri

34:12.170 --> 34:13.500
to have a little bit
of an attitude.

34:13.500 --> 34:16.100
- Well, we knew when we
created Siri that, yes,

34:16.100 --> 34:17.800
we wanted it
to answer questions

34:17.800 --> 34:20.370
and do tasks for you.
But we knew that people

34:20.370 --> 34:23.070
would ask those
funny kinds of questions.

34:23.070 --> 34:26.300
So do you know what
the number one question

34:26.300 --> 34:28.800
that people ask Siri?
I've seen the logs.

34:28.800 --> 34:31.270
- Oh, is it, um, sing for me?

34:31.270 --> 34:33.969
- Very close. That's in the--
that's in the top ten.

34:33.969 --> 34:36.030
- Yes!
- The number one question

34:36.030 --> 34:39.270
that people ask Siri is,
"Do you love me?"

34:39.270 --> 34:40.670
- Aw.

34:40.670 --> 34:43.100
- And we built in
that kind of functionality

34:43.100 --> 34:44.969
into our prototype,
let--let me show you.

34:44.969 --> 34:46.070
- Okay.

34:46.070 --> 34:48.230
- Siri, do you love me?

34:48.230 --> 34:52.070
L-O-V-E.

34:52.070 --> 34:54.199
And Siri says...

34:54.199 --> 34:56.100
- Aw.
- She gives me her heart.

34:56.100 --> 34:59.330
- Aw, that's fantastic.

35:00.830 --> 35:04.530
So have you been performing
magic your whole life as well?

35:04.530 --> 35:07.670
- I--I was really into magic
when I was a kid,

35:07.670 --> 35:09.330
maybe eight to twelve.

35:09.330 --> 35:13.500
And then I went for 35 years
not doing any magic.

35:13.500 --> 35:17.000
And then when my son became
about the age that I was,

35:17.000 --> 35:18.630
we rediscovered magic together

35:18.630 --> 35:20.070
and that's something
we can share.

35:20.070 --> 35:22.000
- All right, well,
I bet he's excited.

35:22.000 --> 35:24.500
Um, all right, well,
let's go to the boys.

35:24.500 --> 35:25.930
- Okay.
- See if you tricked them.

35:25.930 --> 35:28.430
- Oh, Adam, we could--
we could not be more honored.

35:28.430 --> 35:29.930
Thank you so much
for doing our little show.

35:29.930 --> 35:31.330
- The honor is mine.
Thank you.

35:31.330 --> 35:33.430
- It's so great you wanted
to come on. I mean, uh...

35:33.430 --> 35:36.200
Someone that's really,
really been part of

35:36.200 --> 35:38.500
changing our culture,
changing the future.

35:38.500 --> 35:40.500
When I say "our,"
I don't mean Americans,

35:40.500 --> 35:41.830
I mean humanity.

35:41.830 --> 35:44.130
Uh, you've just done so much.

35:44.130 --> 35:45.470
So thrilled
you came on this show,

35:45.470 --> 35:46.600
thank you so much.

35:46.600 --> 35:48.400
Thank you so much
for doing it.

35:49.600 --> 35:52.500
And uh...

35:52.500 --> 35:54.900
You know, I'm trying
to find ways that, eh,

35:54.900 --> 35:58.000
that we have things in common,
'cause you're such a hero.

35:58.000 --> 36:01.230
One way is you--you shuffled cards
a lot like we do some times.

36:01.230 --> 36:03.930
I really liked that a lot,
but I think the best way

36:03.930 --> 36:08.030
to try to figure out how
you did this is to ask Siri.

36:08.030 --> 36:11.670
Hey, Siri!
How did Adam

36:11.670 --> 36:14.870
do that great trick?

36:14.870 --> 36:15.930
- Oh.

36:15.930 --> 36:18.700
I think he used
a circular stack

36:18.700 --> 36:21.370
like Si Stebbins.

36:21.370 --> 36:24.670
- Was it his own--was it one
he developed himself?

36:24.670 --> 36:26.670
- I don't know,
but if he did,

36:26.670 --> 36:29.500
he's even smarter
than I thought he was.

36:34.870 --> 36:38.200
- So, did Siri figure it out?

36:38.200 --> 36:41.530
- Let me actually consult
my favorite expert.

36:41.530 --> 36:44.200
Siri, did we fool them?

36:44.200 --> 36:47.370
F-O-O-L.

36:47.370 --> 36:48.470
Fool.

36:48.470 --> 36:50.130
And Siri says...

36:54.030 --> 36:56.700
- Adam Cheyer!

37:01.570 --> 37:04.270
Coming up, we serve
our main course of magic.

37:04.270 --> 37:06.670
Penn and Teller
perform after the break.

37:18.000 --> 37:19.700
- If there's one thing
Penn and Teller

37:19.700 --> 37:22.570
love more than magic,
it's good cooperage.

37:22.570 --> 37:24.670
While you all
google that word,

37:24.670 --> 37:26.930
let's bring out
Penn and Teller!

37:31.700 --> 37:33.270
- Ooh!

37:33.270 --> 37:35.400
What's this?

37:35.400 --> 37:40.300
We're all staring at a barrel
with things going through it.

37:40.300 --> 37:42.430
One thing I'll say
for Penn and Teller,

37:42.430 --> 37:45.130
they have their finger
on the pulse

37:45.130 --> 37:47.700
of the TV-watching public.

37:47.700 --> 37:51.070
'Cause when we're watching TV,
we demand to see

37:51.070 --> 37:53.400
good cooperage.

37:53.400 --> 37:57.000
And there is some fine barrel
building up on that stage.

37:57.000 --> 38:01.400
Nice bilge.
Good staves.

38:01.400 --> 38:04.800
It's such a peaceful act.

38:04.800 --> 38:08.030
Ooh!
A new character enters.

38:08.030 --> 38:09.970
Who is it?

38:09.970 --> 38:12.970
A target with a balloon,

38:12.970 --> 38:15.270
meets a barrel with things.

38:16.930 --> 38:18.430
Now there's drama.

38:19.670 --> 38:22.030
Suspense.

38:22.030 --> 38:24.570
Conflict.

38:24.570 --> 38:26.030
Action.

38:26.030 --> 38:30.030
The barrel makes its move.

38:30.030 --> 38:31.530
Ha ha!

38:31.530 --> 38:34.130
And the barrel is victorious.

38:34.130 --> 38:38.530
And the target, balloon-less,
skulks off, defeated.

38:39.500 --> 38:41.130
So how are they doing this?

38:41.130 --> 38:43.030
There's no one in the barrel,
not with those things

38:43.030 --> 38:44.400
going through it.

38:44.400 --> 38:47.100
No one behind it.
No one underneath it.

38:47.100 --> 38:49.800
Can't be mechanical
with that bad marksmanship.

38:49.800 --> 38:52.170
So it must be...

38:53.470 --> 38:55.400
a monkey!

38:55.400 --> 38:57.730
There's a monkey in the barrel.

38:57.730 --> 39:01.200
Something very simian
about that barrel.

39:01.200 --> 39:04.330
People love animals
in magic acts.

39:04.330 --> 39:07.200
As long as they're treated
with compassion, dignity,

39:07.200 --> 39:09.130
and respect.
Ooh.

39:09.130 --> 39:10.400
What's happening now?

39:10.400 --> 39:12.030
What's the monkey doing?

39:12.030 --> 39:14.730
Those things do
go all the way through.

39:14.730 --> 39:16.100
Oh.

39:16.100 --> 39:18.570
Now it's a musical piece.

39:18.570 --> 39:20.500
Very free jazz.

39:20.500 --> 39:22.470
Very avant-garde.

39:22.470 --> 39:26.470
Very 21st century classical.

39:26.470 --> 39:28.470
Oh, I get it.

39:28.470 --> 39:32.070
But it's not a monkey.

39:36.070 --> 39:38.170
The big son of a bitch
was in the barrel.

39:42.000 --> 39:43.800
- Ah.
- Wah!

39:43.800 --> 39:45.870
- Oh my goodness.

39:45.870 --> 39:47.470
Wow.

39:48.670 --> 39:51.070
- Penn, that was a great trick.

39:51.070 --> 39:53.170
- No, no, no, no, no.
No, Alyson.

39:53.170 --> 39:55.330
No, no.
That was a good trick.

39:55.330 --> 39:57.000
I'm uh, um...

39:57.000 --> 39:59.970
6 foot 7 inches tall,
weigh 236 pounds.

39:59.970 --> 40:02.530
That's a small barrel,
that is a good trick.

40:02.530 --> 40:04.170
But it's not a great trick.

40:04.170 --> 40:06.000
If that were a great trick,

40:06.000 --> 40:07.830
I would have been
comfortable in the barrel.

40:07.830 --> 40:10.430
- Aw.

40:10.430 --> 40:14.270
We gotta wrap it up.
Good night from "Fool Us."

40:14.270 --> 40:16.670
- Gotta get to that
breakfast buffet.

